  "content": "rvia workspace docs check --help` shows the new command.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(cli): add 'corvia workspace docs check' subcommand\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3.7: Update dashboard `HealthPanel` for new finding types\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `tools/corvia-dashboard/src/components/HealthPanel.tsx`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add styling/labels for new check types**\n\nAdd entries to the `CHECK_LABELS` map using the full `as_str()` keys (matching server output from `CheckType::as_str()`). Note: the existing labels use shortened keys that rely on the fallback — this is a pre-existing issue not addressed here.\n\nThe existing `CHECK_LABELS` type is `Record<string, { label: string; icon: string }>` — match that shape (no `color` property; severity colors are computed from `confidence` via `severityColor()`):\n\n```typescript\n// In CHECK_LABELS map:\nmisplaced_doc: { label: \"Misplaced Doc\", icon: \"📁\" },\ntemporal_contradiction: { label: \"Temporal Contradiction\", icon: \"⚡\" },\ncoverage_gap: { label: \"Coverage Gap\", icon: \"📝\" },\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace\ngit add tools/corvia-dashboard/src/components/HealthPanel.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat(dashboard): render new docs check finding types in HealthPanel\"\n```\n\n---\n\n\n### Task 3.8: Run full test suite and push\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Run all tests**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test --workspace`\nExpected: All tests pass\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Push both repos**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && git push\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace && git push\n```\n\n---\n",
